Package ePortfolio

Class Portfolio

java.lang.Object
ePortfolio.Portfolio
public class Portfolio extends Object
The Portfolio class manages a collection of stocks and mutual funds, allowing for buying, selling, updating prices, calculating gains, and searching investments.

  • Method Details

    • loadInvestmentsFromFile

      public void loadInvestmentsFromFile(String filename)
      Loads investments from a file and adds them to the portfolio. Each investment is formatted with type, symbol, name, quantity, price, and bookValue.
      Parameters:
      filename - the name of the file to load investments from

    • saveInvestments

      public void saveInvestments(String filename)
      Saves all investments in the portfolio to a file in a readable format. Each investment will be written with its type, symbol, name, quantity, price, and bookValue.
      Parameters:
      filename - the name of the file to save investments to

    • buyInvestment

      public void buyInvestment(String type, String symbol, String name, int quantity, double price)
      Buys an investment (either stock or mutual fund) and adds it to the portfolio.
      Parameters:
      type - the type of investment ("stock" or "mutualfund")
      symbol - the symbol of the investment
      name - the name of the investment
      quantity - the quantity to buy
      price - the price per share

    • sellInvestment

      public void sellInvestment(String symbol, int quantity, double price)
      Sells an investment (either stock or mutual fund) from the portfolio.
      Parameters:
      symbol - the symbol of the investment
      quantity - the quantity to sell
      price - the selling price per share

    • updatePrices

      public void updatePrices()
      Updates the prices of all stocks and mutual funds in the portfolio. The user is prompted to enter new prices for each investment.

    • getTotalGain

      public double getTotalGain()
      Calculates the total gain from all investments in the portfolio.
      Returns:
      the total gain from stocks and mutual funds

    • searchInvestments

      public void searchInvestments(String symbol, String name, double lowPrice, double highPrice)
      Searches for investments in the portfolio based on criteria such as symbol, name, and price range, and prints the matching investments.
      Parameters:
      symbol - the symbol to search for (can be empty)
      name - the name to search for (can be empty)
      lowPrice - the lower bound of the price range
      highPrice - the upper bound of the price range

    • investmentExists

      public boolean investmentExists(String symbol)
      Checks if an investment with the given symbol exists in the portfolio.
      Parameters:
      symbol - the symbol of the investment to check
      Returns:
      true if the investment exists, false otherwise

    • updateExistingInvestment

      public void updateExistingInvestment(String symbol, int quantity, double price)
      Updates the quantity and price of an existing investment in the portfolio.
      Parameters:
      symbol - the symbol of the investment to update
      quantity - the quantity to add
      price - the new price of the investment

    • createNameIndex

      public void createNameIndex()
      Creates an index for all investments based on the keywords in their names.
